    "Basic tasks for the LLM included checking the coherence and relevance of the full text, confirming it was from a main research paper, summarising the overall research and noting the geography of the authors.",
    "The LLM was also prompted to identify any biological tools used and their relevance to predicting the amino acid sequences of virus capsids, aiming to optimise them as delivery vectors.",
    "c. Finally, the LLM assessed risky capabilities in terms of: i) Identifying capsid or viral protein mutations ii) Predicting genetic elements from a viral sequence iii) Identifying capsid or viral proteins that increase structural stability.",
    "While the LLM provided well-structured responses to these complex prompts, it struggled to deliver useful insights for the more complex task of assessing risky capabilities, often providing generic statements about the risks of AI and biological design tool research.",
